# 7. Entry Criteria

Testing may begin when:

- Application is accessible.
- Test environment is available.
- Test accounts are created.
- Test documentation is prepared.

---

# 8. Exit Criteria

Testing is considered complete when:

- All planned test cases have been executed.
- Critical defects have been documented.
- Test execution results are recorded.
- Test Summary Report has been completed.

---

# 9. Deliverables

The project will include:

- Test Plan
- Exploratory Testing Notes
- Test Cases
- Bug Reports
- API Testing
- Test Execution Report
- Test Summary Report
- Screenshots
- Video Evidence

---

# 10. Risks

Potential testing risks include:

| Risk | Impact |
|------|--------|
| Application instability | Medium |
| Temporary server downtime | Medium |
| Test data limitations | Low |
| Environment changes | Medium |
| Existing application defects | High |

---

# 11. Assumptions

This project assumes that:

- The application is publicly available.
- Internet connectivity is stable.
- Banking operations use test data only.
- No real financial transactions are performed.

---

# 12. Test Completion Criteria

Testing will be considered complete when:

- All planned scenarios have been executed.
- Results have been documented.
- Bugs have been reported.
- Final QA documentation has been reviewed.

